\begin_layout Section
Baseline Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The baseline equilibrium shows moderate entrepreneurship (0.1472 overall),
 with substantial heterogeneity by education.
 Entry is highest for high education (0.1618) and lowest for middle education (0.1398),
 while average labor demand is 21.9129 workers and rises steeply with skill from 9.7237 (low) to 33.5470 (high).
 This pattern indicates that high-education entrepreneurs operate at much larger scale even when their entry rate is only modestly above other groups.
 Labor-market transitions also suggest strong persistence in employment (Employed 
\begin_inset Formula $\rightarrow$
\end_inset

 Work = 0.740) and a small unemployment-to-entrepreneurship channel (0.002),
 so necessity entry is present but limited in the baseline.
\end_layout

